# Component Organization

Components are organized in a feature-based structure inside [src/components](mdc:src/components).

## Component Categories

- [src/components/ui](mdc:src/components/ui) - Reusable UI components based on shadcn/ui (buttons, cards, etc.)
- [src/components/layout](mdc:src/components/layout) - Layout components (header, footer, navigation, etc.)
- [src/components/blog](mdc:src/components/blog) - Blog-specific components
- [src/components/home](mdc:src/components/home) - Homepage-specific components
- [src/components/servers](mdc:src/components/servers) - Server-related components
- [src/components/tools](mdc:src/components/tools) - Tool-related components

## Component Conventions

1. Components should be created in their respective feature folders
2. Use TypeScript for all components
3. Prefer functional components with hooks
4. Use the `ui` directory for shared, reusable UI components
5. Feature-specific components should go in their respective directories
